Text.Value: Well! These must be important birds indeed, Mr Dekarios. Forgive me for feasting on their bodies and bones so very voraciously.
Oh, but that reminds me! I've found you something. A lovely little keepsake. In the past it might've helped with your condition, but now that you're better, perhaps you can put it to some other use.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [MATV] *REUSE* CAT_Rig_CINE_LickPaws_01 or Sit_Idle_01 (with Tressym wings attached)
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera shows the ring and the letters at Tara's feet.

Text.Value: More or less. But the city is still in danger.
I haven't. In fact, I've got a great deal more to eat, indeed. And neither you nor anyone else is going to stop me, Mr Dekarios. Tara away!
You're lucky I adore you, you mutton-head.
My, is that a ring? For us? You shouldn't have.
You love it, don't you, sir? Like a fish in water.
She's agreed. Just about.
I suppose you won't be terribly shocked to find your old friend Tara amongst the pigeons. They've always been a personal favourite.
Leave.
Mr Dekarios! Heavens, fancy seeing you here!
Until then, all on the up and up with you, sir?

I'll be on my way, then. There are a few places in the city I'd like to visit. I might've sussed some interesting items I'd rather like to get my paws upon. If I find anything interesting, I might even be willing to share.
There's a much better aviary across town, if you've already picked over the choice cuts here.
Gale, she's been eating those missing courier pigeons. Tell her to stop!
She isn't my tressym. She's my friend. And from the looks of things, it appears she's eating pigeons.
Time to move along, Tara. If you get caught here, you'll be in trouble.
Enjoy your feast, Tara.
Perhaps while I'm seeking out this new feasthall, I'll pay a few visits around town. I might've sussed some interesting items I'd rather like to get my paws upon.
Mr Dekarios! Heavens, fancy seeing you here!
Tara, I don't suppose you're responsible for the missing messenger pigeons...
Importance is relative. A letter may be important to one; a growling belly may be more important to another.
*Hiss!*
Can you ask her to stop eating pigeons?
Hop to it, then, sir. Imminent peril is terrible for my digestion.
If I find anything interesting, I might even be willing to share.
Oh no. I'm chastened.
No, but I am going to make you very sorry if you don't stop.
Another aviary, you say? Well, that does sound quite interesting. The brood here is getting a little thin.
Well! These must be important birds indeed, Mr Dekarios. Forgive me for feasting on their bodies and bones so very voraciously.
I suppose you won't be terribly shocked to find your old friend Tara amongst the pigeons. They've always been a personal favourite.
I know, I know, but I just love you so.
No more pigeons, Tara. They have an important job to do.
Up to my eyeballs in drama, deceit, and subterfuge. Nothing unusual.
I'd offer you some of your favourite meat, but I haven't got any. Beholder jerky is surprisingly hard to come by.
You aren't going to scold me, are you, sir?
In actual fact, I'm going to eat them up even faster and more voraciously than I did before. How about that?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: TAra eats all the pigeons after this

Text.Value: I'll see you soon, I'm sure, Mr Dekarios. Do take care of yourself, all right?
Anyone who tries to remove me will be in far worse trouble, I assure you.
One needn't guess. Pigeon meat is my second-favourite.
*Grrmm...*

EditorData.SFXTags: Annoyed, but agrees to stop eating Pigeons [DP]

Text.Value: Very well. Enjoy your feast, Tara.
Thank you. I most certainly will, sir.
Leave.
What's your tressym doing here, Gale?
*Riaow!*
For me? You shouldn't have.
Actually, Mr Dekarios, I think the sorry one will be you.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: TAra launches a magic missle/ fireball at Gale

Text.Value: Enjoy yourself now, Tara. Looks like you've got yourself set up quite nicely here.
I am. Stop that, Tara! You need to leave the pigeons be.
For me? You shouldn't have.
Hang on - isn't this where the post house's courier pigeons roost? I don't suppose you've been eating them...
We'll catch up later, Tara - there's no time now.
*Meow!*
More's the pity. But no bother. These pigeons are quite delicious.
I'd offer you some of your favourite meat, but I haven't got any. Beholder jerky is surprisingly hard to come by.
Tara, I don't suppose you're responsible for the missing messenger pigeons...
Hang on - isn't this where the post house's courier pigeons roost? Should she be eating them?
Tara! That can't be you, can it?
Oh. Right. Did you hear that, Tara? Erm. Stop it.

Synopsis: Player approaches Tara and sees she is carrying an item. Player tries to convince Tara to give the item over. If Gale is in party he will be favoured speaker and will recognize Tara and why she has a magic item with her.
